    {
      "id": "overview",
      "title": "Role Overview",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "DevOps/SRE interviews test your infrastructure knowledge, automation skills, and ability to build reliable, scalable systems. Expect hands-on troubleshooting scenarios and system design questions."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**What interviewers assess:**\n\n- Linux/Unix systems knowledge\n- Cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure)\n- CI/CD and automation\n- Monitoring, alerting, and incident response\n- Infrastructure as Code (Terraform, etc.)"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "format",
      "title": "Common Interview Format",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Typical DevOps/SRE interview loop:**\n\n1. **Recruiter screen** (30 min)\n2. **Technical phone screen** (60 min) - Troubleshooting or coding\n3. **Onsite/Virtual loop** (4-5 hours):\n   - System design/architecture round\n   - Troubleshooting/debugging scenario\n   - Coding/automation round\n   - Behavioral round"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "For troubleshooting scenarios, explain your methodology: how you'd gather information, form hypotheses, and systematically narrow down the issue."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
